UID:20251209T090000-FlightStudy-Day2@artem
DTSTAMP:20251207T210000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20251209T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20251209T092000
SUMMARY:Flight Study – Day 2: Radio Discipline
DESCRIPTION:Focus: Radio workflow and no-talking departure.\n- Simulate ATIS → Ground → Tower → Departure calls.\n- Practice pre-loading the next frequency in STANDBY before flip-flop.\n- Drill: No talking from takeoff roll until Tower hands you to Departure.\n- Always reset ATIS volume after copying.
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20251210T090000-FlightStudy-Day3@artem
DTSTAMP:20251207T210000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20251210T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20251210T092000
SUMMARY:Flight Study – Day 3: Maneuver Setup
DESCRIPTION:Focus: Pre-maneuver checklist and headings.\n- Pre-Maneuver Checklist: Fuel BOTH\, Mixture RICH\, Carb heat ON\, Landing light ON\, Clearing turns COMPLETE.\n- Practice bugging headings before steep turns\, slow flight\, and climbs/descents.\n- Visualize clearing turns and setup flow before each maneuver.
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20251211T090000-FlightStudy-Day4@artem
DTSTAMP:20251207T210000Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20251211T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20251211T092000
SUMMARY:Flight Study – Day 4: Landings & Confidence
DESCRIPTION:Focus: Landings\, power control\, and confidence.\n- Visualize full pattern: downwind → base → final → flare.\n- Practice looking far down the runway during flare.\n- Mentally rehearse smooth\, stable power changes on final.\n- Reminder: “The plane is in your hands” – commit to decisions and relax grip.
END:VEVENT

